==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Provender
<hw>Prov"en*der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>provende</ets>, F. <ets>provende</ets>, provisions, provender, fr.
LL. <ets>praebenda</ets> (<ets>prae</ets> and <ets>pro</ets> being
confused), a daily allowance of provisions, a prebend. See
<er>Prebend</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Dry food for domestic animals,
as hay, straw, corn, oats, or a mixture of ground grain; feed.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Hay or other <xex>provender</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Good <qex>provender</qex> laboring horses would have.</q>
<rj><qau>Tusser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Food or provisions.</def> <mark>[R or
Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provenience</ent>⟦br⟧
